@page "/"

<PageTitle>Quark Suite - Home</PageTitle>

<Div Class="max-w-4xl space-y-8">
    <Div Class="space-y-3">
        <H1 Class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight">Introduction</H1>
        <Paragraph Class="text-base leading-7 text-muted-foreground" Margin="Margin.Is0">
            Quark Suite is a set of beautifully designed, accessible components and utilities for Blazor.
            It follows the same principles as shadcn/ui: open code, composable primitives, and sensible defaults.
        </Paragraph>
    </Div>

    <Div Class="space-y-4">
        <Paragraph Class="text-base leading-7 text-muted-foreground" Margin="Margin.Is0">
            This is not a traditional component package that hides implementation details. The goal is to give you
            building blocks you can read, extend, and adapt directly to your application.
        </Paragraph>
        <Paragraph Class="text-base leading-7 text-muted-foreground" Margin="Margin.Is0">
            The demo project mirrors a documentation-first layout so you can browse every surface and form primitive
            the same way you would in a docs site.
        </Paragraph>
    </Div>

    <Div Class="space-y-3">
        <H2 Class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Core ideas</H2>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-base leading-7 text-muted-foreground">
            <li><span class="font-medium text-foreground">Open code</span>: Use and modify component source directly.</li>
            <li><span class="font-medium text-foreground">Composition</span>: Components are small and predictable.</li>
            <li><span class="font-medium text-foreground">Distribution</span>: Keep schema and command-line workflows simple.</li>
            <li><span class="font-medium text-foreground">AI-ready</span>: Clean structures that are easy for tools and people to inspect.</li>
        </ul>
    </Div>

    <Div Class="space-y-3">
        <H2 Class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Open code</H2>
        <Paragraph Class="text-base leading-7 text-muted-foreground" Margin="Margin.Is0">
            Components are designed to be copied and tailored. You can start with defaults, then tune classes,
            variants, and behavior as your design system evolves.
        </Paragraph>
        <Div Class="rounded-lg border border-border bg-muted/50 p-4">
            <pre class="text-sm overflow-x-auto"><code>&lt;Field&gt;
    &lt;FieldLabel For="email"&gt;Email&lt;/FieldLabel&gt;
    &lt;FieldBody&gt;
        &lt;Input Type="email" Placeholder="you@example.com" /&gt;
    &lt;/FieldBody&gt;
&lt;/Field&gt;

&lt;Button Variant="ButtonVariant.Default"&gt;Continue&lt;/Button&gt;</code></pre>
        </Div>
    </Div>

    <Div Class="space-y-4">
        <H2 Class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Continue exploring</H2>
        <Div Class="flex gap-3 flex-wrap">
            <Button Type="ButtonType.Link" To="getting-started" Variant="ButtonVariant.Default">Getting Started</Button>
            <Button Type="ButtonType.Link" To="components" Variant="ButtonVariant.Outline">Components</Button>
            <Button Type="ButtonType.Link" To="forms/input-demo" Variant="ButtonVariant.Outline">Forms</Button>
            <Button Type="ButtonType.Link" To="surfaces/cards" Variant="ButtonVariant.Outline">Surfaces</Button>
        </Div>
    </Div>
</Div>
